Vice President Mike Pence addressed the United Nations Security Council and called on the UN to recognize Juan Guaidó as the legitimate President of Venezuela. He urged the UN to revoke the credentials of Venezuela's representative to the UN and seat Guaidó's representative in his place. Pence emphasized that Nicolás Maduro is a dictator with no legitimate claim to power and called for his removal. He also discussed the US's stance on Iran, stating that the US will continue to confront Iran's malign influence in the Middle East. Pence reiterated that all options are on the table regarding Venezuela, including military intervention, and urged Russia to cease its support for the Maduro regime.